| Notes                   = 
* A recurring theme of this team is their difficulty with naming:
** '''Great Lakes Avengers''' or '''GLA''' - Observing that there were already [[Avengers (Earth-616)|East Coast]] and [[West Coast Avengers]], [[Craig Hollis (Earth-616)|Mr. Immortal]] dubbed his new team the ''Great Lakes Avengers''.{{r|G.L.A. Vol 1 1}}{{r|West Coast Avengers Vol 2 46}} This name brought on the scrutiny of [[Clinton Barton (Earth-616)|Hawkeye]],{{r|West Coast Avengers Vol 2 46}} but later they were granted official permission from [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]] the title.{{r|Avengers West Coast Vol 1 48}} Although they continue to change their name, this is the most common title used.
*** '''Midwest Avengers''' - Upon first hearing their name, [[Vision (Earth-616)|Vision]] asked "''"Great Lakes?" Would not "Midwest" be a more appropriate nomenclature...?''"{{r|Avengers West Coast Vol 2 49}}
** '''Lightning Rods''' - When they got an official sanction to become the Midwest branch of the [[Thunderbolts (Earth-616)|Thunderbolts]], the team was redubbed ''Lightning Rods''.{{r|Deadpool Vol 3 10}}{{r|Thunderbolts Vol 1 15|17}}
** '''Superhuman Warriors Operation Redistribution Division''' or '''S.W.O.R.D.''' -  When it was revealed that the Thunderbolts were secretly the [[Masters of Evil (Earth-616)|Masters of Evil]], [[Craig Hollis (Earth-616)|Mr. Immortal]] ventured becoming an official branch of [[Strategic Homeland Intervention, Enforcement and Logistics Division (Earth-616)|S.H.I.E.L.D.]] named ''[[S.W.O.R.D.]]'' "''the Superhuman Warriors Operation...Redistribution Division''".{{r|Thunderbolts Vol 1 15|17}}
** '''Great Lakes X-Men''' or '''GLX''' - When the team members realized they were all [[Homo superior|mutants]], they decided to become the ''[[X-Men|Great Lakes X-Men]]''.{{r|G.L.A. Vol 1 4}}{{r|GLX-Mas Special Vol 1 1}} When [[Rachel Summers (Earth-811)|Marvel Girl]] heard they were calling themselves X-Men, she [[Telepathy|telepathically]] influenced Mr. Immortal into changing it.{{r|Thing Vol 2 8}}
** '''Great Lakes Defenders''' or '''GLD''' - Mr. Immortal only briefly suggested name the ''Great Lakes Defenders'' before [[Stephen Strange (Earth-616)|Doctor Strange]] [[Magic|magically]] influenced him into changing it.{{r|Thing Vol 2 8}}
** '''Great Lakes Champions''' or '''GLC''' - After winning the [[Benjamin Grimm (Earth-616)|Thing]]'s superhero poker tournament and breaking out into a chorus of [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/We_Are_the_Champions Queen's "We Are The Champions"], Mr. Immortal decide to call the team ''Great Lakes Champions'' over the objections of [[Hercules Panhellenios (Earth-616)|Hercules]].{{r|Thing Vol 2 8}}{{r|Cable & Deadpool Vol 1 30}}
** '''Great Lakes Initiative''' or '''GLI''' - After eagerly signing up under the [[Superhuman Registration Act]], the team became the official government-sanctioned protectors of [[Wisconsin (State)|Wisconsin]], the ''[[Great Lakes Initiative]]''.{{r|Cable & Deadpool Vol 1 30}}{{r|Avengers: The Initiative Vol 1 19}}{{r|Avengers: The Initiative Vol 1 25}}
** '''Great Lakes Power Pack''' - This title was used humorously with multiple past titles of the team.{{r|Fear Itself: The Home Front Vol 1 6}}
** '''America's Alpha Flight''' - According to Flatman, an anonymous person online dubbed the team "''America's [[Alpha Flight]]''".{{r|Great Lakes Avengers Vol 1 5}}
| Trivia                  = 
* Members of the Great Lakes Avengers were summoned into battle as [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]] during the [[Avengers/JLA|Avengers/JLA crossover]]. [[Val Ventura (Earth-616)|Flatman]] was defeated by [[w:c:DC:Chad Graham (New Earth)|Prometheus]], but was saved by the [[Henry McCoy (Earth-616)|Beast]]. [[Ashley Crawford (Earth-616)|Big Bertha]] aided [[w:c:DC:Diana of Themyscira (New Earth)|Wonder Woman]] in the final battle.{{r|JLA/Avengers Vol 1 4}}
* The 2005 GLA mini-series parodied the dark comic events ''Identity Crisis'' and ''[[Avengers Disassembled]]''. This miniseries was also a parody of comic book deaths, and it had been announced that a team member would die every issue.

